---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="CIBIL Score for Personal Loan | Minimum Score & Impact | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/pages/credit-score">Credit Score</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>CIBIL Score for Personal Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>CIBIL Score for <span class="gradient-text">Personal Loan</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Learn the minimum CIBIL score required for personal loan approval, how your score impacts interest rates, and strategies to qualify even with a lower score.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
          <span>Minimum Score: 650+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Best Rates at 750+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Up to ₹40 Lakh</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">

          <!-- Overview -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Overview</span>
              <h2>How CIBIL Score Affects Personal Loan Approval</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Your CIBIL score is the single most important factor that determines whether your personal loan application gets approved or rejected. Since personal loans are unsecured (no collateral required), lenders rely heavily on your credit score to assess the risk of lending to you.</p>
            <p>Most banks and NBFCs require a minimum CIBIL score of 650 to 700 for personal loan approval. However, having a score of 750 or above significantly improves your chances and gives you access to the lowest interest rates, highest loan amounts, and fastest processing times.</p>
            <p>Your score doesn't just determine approval — it directly influences the interest rate you'll pay. A difference of just 50 points in your CIBIL score can mean a 2–4% difference in interest rates, which translates to thousands of rupees in savings or extra cost over the loan tenure.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Score-wise Impact Table -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Score Impact</span>
              <h2>Personal Loan Eligibility by CIBIL Score</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Here's a detailed breakdown of how different CIBIL score ranges impact your personal loan application across key parameters.</p>
            <table class="rate-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>CIBIL Score</th>
                  <th>Interest Rate</th>
                  <th>Max Loan Amount</th>
                  <th>Approval Chances</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>800–900</strong></td>
                  <td><span style="color: #22c55e; font-weight: 600;">10.25% – 12%</span></td>
                  <td>Up to ₹40 Lakh</td>
                  <td>Almost guaranteed</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>750–799</strong></td>
                  <td><span style="color: #22c55e; font-weight: 600;">12% – 15%</span></td>
                  <td>Up to ₹30 Lakh</td>
                  <td>Very high</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>700–749</strong></td>
                  <td><span style="color: #3b82f6; font-weight: 600;">15% – 19%</span></td>
                  <td>Up to ₹20 Lakh</td>
                  <td>High</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>650–699</strong></td>
                  <td><span style="color: #f59e0b; font-weight: 600;">19% – 24%</span></td>
                  <td>Up to ₹10 Lakh</td>
                  <td>Moderate</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>550–649</strong></td>
                  <td><span style="color: #f97316; font-weight: 600;">24% – 36%</span></td>
                  <td>Up to ₹5 Lakh</td>
                  <td>Low (NBFCs only)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Below 550</strong></td>
                  <td><span style="color: #ef4444; font-weight: 600;">Usually rejected</span></td>
                  <td>N/A</td>
                  <td>Very unlikely</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <!-- Eligibility Factors -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Eligibility</span>
              <h2>Factors Beyond CIBIL Score That Affect Approval</h2>
            </div>
            <p>While CIBIL score is crucial, lenders also evaluate several other factors when processing your personal loan application. Meeting these criteria alongside a good score maximises your approval chances.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Monthly Income & Employment Stability</strong>
                  <p>Most lenders require a minimum monthly income of ₹20,000–₹25,000 for salaried individuals. A stable job with the same employer for at least 1–2 years strengthens your application significantly.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Debt-to-Income Ratio (DTI)</strong>
                  <p>Lenders prefer a DTI ratio below 40–50%. This means your total monthly EMI obligations (including the new loan) should not exceed 40–50% of your monthly income.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Existing Loan Obligations</strong>
                  <p>Multiple active loans reduce your repayment capacity in the lender's assessment. If you already have 3–4 running EMIs, approval becomes harder regardless of your CIBIL score.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Age & Loan Tenure</strong>
                  <p>Most lenders require borrowers to be between 21–60 years of age. The loan tenure must end before you turn 60 (or 65 for some lenders), affecting the maximum tenure available.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Company & Industry Category</strong>
                  <p>Salaried employees of top-tier companies (Category A) get preferential rates and higher loan amounts. Government employees and PSU workers are also considered low-risk borrowers.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Banking Relationship</strong>
                  <p>Having a salary account or existing relationship with the lending bank often results in pre-approved offers with lower interest rates and minimal documentation requirements.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Steps to Get Approved -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">How to Qualify</span>
              <h2>Steps to Get a Personal Loan Approved</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Follow these steps to maximise your chances of getting a personal loan approved at the best possible interest rate.</p>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <h3>Check Your CIBIL Score</h3>
                <p>Start by checking your CIBIL score for free on TrueCred. If it's below 700, work on improving it before applying. Even a 30–50 point increase can significantly impact your interest rate.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <h3>Compare Lender Offers</h3>
                <p>Don't apply blindly. Compare personal loan offers from multiple banks and NBFCs based on your score range. Use TrueCred's comparison tool to find the best rates without triggering multiple hard inquiries.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <h3>Prepare Your Documents</h3>
                <p>Keep PAN card, Aadhaar card, salary slips (last 3 months), bank statements (last 6 months), and employment proof ready. Complete documentation speeds up processing.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">4</div>
                <h3>Apply & Track Progress</h3>
                <p>Submit your application with the best-matched lender. Track the status in real-time. Most lenders provide instant or same-day approval for scores above 750 with complete documentation.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">

          <!-- Check Score Form -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Check Loan Eligibility</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="PAN Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="date" class="form-input" placeholder="Date of Birth" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Check Eligibility <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
              <p class="form-disclaimer">
                <i class="fas fa-lock"></i> 100% safe & secure. No impact on your score.
              </p>
            </form>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Links -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <ul class="sidebar-links">
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Free Credit Score</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/cibil-score-pan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> CIBIL Check by PAN</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/increase-cibil-score"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Increase CIBIL Score</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/cibil-score-credit-card"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> CIBIL for Credit Card</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/cibil-dispute"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Raise CIBIL Dispute</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Personal Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Cards</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> EMI Calculators</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About CIBIL Score for Personal Loan</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What is the minimum CIBIL score for a personal loan?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Most banks require a minimum CIBIL score of 700–750 for personal loan approval. However, some NBFCs and fintech lenders may approve loans for scores as low as 550–650, but at significantly higher interest rates (24–36% p.a.). For the best rates and highest approval chances, a score of 750 or above is recommended.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I get a personal loan with a CIBIL score of 600?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, it is possible to get a personal loan with a CIBIL score of 600, but your options will be limited. Some NBFCs like Bajaj Finserv, Tata Capital, and fintech lenders like MoneyTap or KreditBee offer personal loans to applicants with lower scores. Expect higher interest rates (20–30%), lower loan amounts (₹50,000–₹5 lakh), and shorter tenures. Adding a co-applicant with a good score can improve your chances.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>How much interest difference does a CIBIL score of 750 vs 650 make?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>The difference can be substantial. With a CIBIL score of 750+, you may get a personal loan at 11–14% interest. With a score of 650, the rate could be 20–24%. On a ₹5 lakh loan for 3 years, this difference means paying approximately ₹45,000–₹80,000 more in total interest. That's why improving your score before applying can save you significant money.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Does applying for a personal loan reduce my CIBIL score?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, each personal loan application triggers a hard inquiry on your credit report, which can reduce your score by 5–15 points. Multiple applications within a short period compound this effect and also signal "credit-hungry" behaviour to lenders. To avoid this, use TrueCred's comparison tool to shortlist the best lender first, and apply to only one or two at most.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>How can I improve my chances if my CIBIL score is borderline?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>If your CIBIL score is in the 650–700 range, several strategies can improve your approval chances: apply with your salary bank where you have a relationship; choose a lender with lower score requirements; provide additional income proof (rental income, investments); add a co-applicant with a higher score; opt for a lower loan amount with a shorter tenure; and ensure all existing EMIs are being paid on time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Check Your Personal Loan Eligibility</h2>
      <p>Find out your CIBIL score and get matched with the best personal loan offers for your profile. Free, instant, and zero impact on your score.</p>
      <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
        Check Eligibility Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
